==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Derotremata
<hw>Der`o*tre"ma*ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>de`ros</grk> skin + <grk>trh^ma</grk>, <grk>trh^mata</grk>,
hole.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The tribe of aquatic Amphibia which
includes Amphiuma, Menopoma, etc. They have permanent gill openings, but
no external gills; -- called also <fam>Cryptobranchiata</fam>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>Derotrema</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Derre</ent>⟦br⟧
